The paper deals with sparsification techniques for uncertain graphs, which are prevalent in several applications including communications systems, biological databases, and social networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes sparsification techniques that preserve the underlying structure of the graph while reducing its size. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper mentions social networks as one of the applications of uncertain graphs. 

cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper mentions biological databases as one of the applications of uncertain graphs. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with uncertainty in graphs, which is a common problem in control systems. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes techniques that can be used to efficiently and accurately approximate any query and mining tasks on the original graph, which is a common problem in machine learning.
